==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subnuvolar
<hw>Sub*nu"vo*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>sub</ets> + It. <ets>nuvola</ets> cloud: cf. L.
<ets>subnubilus</ets> somewhat cloudy.]</ety> <def>Under the clouds;
attended or partly covered or obscured by clouds; somewhat cloudy.</def>
<mark>[R. & Poetic]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Subnuvolar</qex> lights of evening sharply slant.</q>
<rj><qau>Milnes.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subobscurely</ent>⟦br⟧
